# Contributing to Ant Swarming Statistics API

We welcome contributions from everyone. Here are some guidelines to follow to help us manage the project efficiently.

## Types of Contributions

- **Feature Requests**: Suggest new features for the project.
- **Bug Fixes**: Report and fix bugs in the project.
- **Enhancements**: Suggest and implement improvements to the existing codebase.
- **Documentation**: Add or improve documentation.
- **Tests**: Add or improve tests.
- **Bug Reports**: Report issues or unexpected behaviors.
- **Code Reviews**: Help review pull requests from other contributors.

## Submission Process

1. **Open an Issue**: Before working on a contribution, please open an issue to discuss the proposed change.
2. **Submit a Pull Request (PR)**: Once the issue is discussed and agreed upon, you can submit a PR. Make sure to reference the issue in your PR.

## Code Standards

- Ensure that each endpoint created is covered by a test using Bruno. See [docs/en/test.md](/docs/en/test.md) for details.
- Each PR must be free of bugs. It is essential to test thoroughly and take care to ensure the quality of your contribution.

## Environment Setup

Follow the instructions in the [README.md](/README.md) file to set up your development environment.

## Code of Conduct

- **Respect Privacy**: Respect the privacy of other contributors.
- **Bug-Free PRs**: Each PR must be free of bugs. It is crucial to ensure this by testing and being careful.

## Code Review Process

- Only the lead maintainer can approve a PR, but comments and reviews from everyone are welcome.

## License

By contributing, you agree that your contributions will be licensed under the MIT License, as specified in the [LICENSE](/LICENSE) file.

Thank you for contributing to the Ant Swarming Statistics API!
